Tcl's string quoting conventions also try to force you to use K&R style for procedure bodies. e.g<p><pre><code>   proc foo {x} {
      # do stuff
   }
</code></pre>
but if you really want to get around this you can abuse the continuation character<p><pre><code>   proc foo {x} \n   {
      # do stuff
   }</code></pre>
